The compiler warning about &quot;levels of indirection&quot; should have tipped you off. The function should be 

    void transpose(double matrix[][5], int size)

and the other `*` stars should be removed too.

    transposed[j][i] = matrix[i][j];
    ...
    matrix[i][j] = transposed[i][j];

&lt;HR&gt;
Aside: your loop control limits are not idiomatic. This `i&lt;=size-1;` is better as `i&lt;size;` (and can be wrong).

Where you have hard coded the limit such as `j&lt;=4` it is not immediately apparent that this is actually `5-1` and if you had used `j&lt;5` that would be more obvious that it is the same `5` as in the array dimension.

Should you decide to replace that dimension with a `#define` or a `const int` value, you&#39;ll have to hunt down the `4`s and well as the `5`s.

